Here is a simple C++ program that reads a text file line by line and counts the number of occurrences of a specific word in the file:

```
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <string>

int main()
{
    std::ifstream inputFile("inputFile.txt");
    if (!inputFile)
    {
        std::cerr << "Error opening file." << std::endl;
        return 1;
    }

    std::string word;
    int count = 0;

    while (std::getline(inputFile, word))
    {
        if (word == "my_word")
        {
            ++count;
        }
    }

    std::cout << "The number of occurrences of my_word in the text file is " << count << std::endl;

    inputFile.close();
    return 0;
}
```

To use this program, you would first need to create a text file that contains the word you want to count and save it in a location that is accessible to the program. For example, you could create a file called `inputFile.txt` and add the following text:

`my_word my_word my_word my_word my_word my_word my_word my_word my_word my_word my_word my_word my_word my_word my_word my_word my_word my_word my_word`

Then run the program and it will output the number of occurrences of the word `my_word` in the text file.
